Hi there! To write an if/then statement in C, you first need to use the if keyword followed by a condition in parentheses. If the condition is true, the code inside the curly braces will be executed. Here's an example:

if (age >= 18) {
  // Code to be executed if the condition is true
}

In this example, if the age variable is equal to or greater than 18, the code inside the curly braces will be executed.

